<p>The first season, while still worth watching, posts an average episode
rating of 8.5 and all episodes fall within 0.6 of the average.</p>

<p>Anyway, here are the charts that I created.</p>

<div class="language-r highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c1">#beeswarm package required--install.packages('beeswarm')</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="n">library</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">beeswarm</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="w">

</span><span class="n">tvraw</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">read.csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"../data/superhero-tv/supertv.csv"</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="w">

</span><span class="c1">#standalone bee swarm plot </span><span class="w">
</span><span class="n">beeswarm</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Rating</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">~</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">Show</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">data</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">tvraw</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">pch</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="m">16</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">col</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="o">:</span><span class="m">5</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w">
         </span><span class="n">main</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="s1">'IMDb Episode Ratings'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">xlab</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="w">
</span></code></pre></div></div>

